    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-11T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="618"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">261.1122/3–1150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barbour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-11T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 11, 1950—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>815. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 706, February 28.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d618fn1">Not printed, but see the first footnote 1, <ref
                            target="#pg_1114">p. 1114</ref>.</note> Embassy letter to Anna Spiegel,
                    notifying her <gloss target="#t_MFA1">MFA</gloss>’s decision to permit her to
                    depart USSR, <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> February 28 returned
                    undelivered with postal notation: “Addressee departed destination unknown.”</p>
                <p>Of the five persons allegedly permitted to depart USSR, Henry Blacha, Valentina
                    and Vladimir Kazun have “stated” refusal to return USA and desire to remain
                    USSR, Spiegel has not been located, and Adele Sagatas has not replied to Embassy
                    letter.</p>
                <p>Suggest relatives in USA be notified that Embassy is doing everything possible to
                    effect repatriation of these persons but that good faith on part of <gloss
                        target="#t_MFA1">MFA</gloss> in this matter is doubted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barbour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
